<TEXTAREA NAME="ReplyMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">[QUOTE]Originally posted by Lalu:
[B]As a Raid Cleric, you have to be aware of alot of game mechanics not just who do i heal in my group. Also who do you heal first vs who can wait for a heal. Also a side note for the first poster, IF you are just entering NTOV be aware of low health aggro. Once any Player gets to below about 30% health, not matter how much aggro your tank has it will turn on that person. 

Biggest piece a raid cleric can learn, especially when you do raids with less then one cleric per group is Assist Heal. Assist healing will help all your clerics sustain there mana better and speed up the raid in general.

Lalu
High Priestess
GM of Tindi'Losi of the Rathe[/B][/QUOTE]

